@*
    ACKNOWLEDGE PROMPT  (player profile only — Game-UI.md "Where prompts surface")
    A static-backdrop modal driven by the engine's AcknowledgePrompt: title, body,
    and a single "Okay" button that submits an (empty) AcknowledgeResponse. Markup
    only; all behaviour (show/hide on PromptOpened/PromptClosed, submit) lives in
    /scripts/InGame/Prompts/acknowledge-prompt.js. The element ids below are that
    script's contract — keep them in sync.

    Styled as a secondary card: secondary-bordered content with a secondary header.
*@
<div class="modal fade" id="acknowledgeModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="acknowledgeTitle"
     aria-hidden="true" data-bs-backdrop="static" data-bs-keyboard="false">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class="modal-content border border-secondary border-2">
            <div class="modal-header text-bg-secondary border-0">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="acknowledgeTitle"></h5>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p class="mb-0" id="acknowledgeBody"></p>
                <div class="alert alert-warning d-none mt-3 mb-0" id="acknowledgeError" role="alert"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary w-100" id="acknowledgeSubmit">Okay</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>